  "body": "\r\n### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/3dbad6b8ea82b2f325b3fce6d96a7f0dc2b5642f/p2p/chain.py#L775-L782\r\n\r\nThe algorithm linked above and included here is not generating block numbers according to protocol.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nif reverse:\r\n    low = max(0, block_number - limit)\r\n    high = block_number + 1\r\n    block_numbers = reversed(range(low, high, step))\r\nelse:\r\n    low = block_number\r\n    high = block_number + limit\r\nblock_numbers = range(low, high, step)\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor example, if requesting `5` headers starting at block number `0`, with a skip of `1`:\r\n\r\n- expected correct: `0, 2, 4, 6, 8`\r\n- actual: `0, 2, 4` (doesn't return 5 headers)\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nNeed to fix how the limits are computed to take into account the skip size so that we still return the appropriate number of headers.",
